52. No action, suit, prosecution or any other proceeding shall lie or
be brought, instituted or maintained in any court against—
(a) the Government;
(b) the Minister;
(c) the Director General;
(d) any member of the Council or committee; or
(e) any person lawfully acting on behalf of the Council,
in respect of any act, neglect or default done or omitted by him or it
in good faith, in such capacity.
